living in poverty children not receiving high quality early childhood experiences in time of critical brain development there are marginalized segments of the population in addition to those in poverty people of color lgbtq minorities by religion ehtnicity do not always feel welcome and included in our area the macro culture is strong and can create a sense of being an outsider i think many in our society have ironically grown more isolated in a time of greater connectivity partly due to the digital divide and partly due to fewer face to face interactions we have not built our community physically for walkability and sociability we designed an auto dependent infrastructure that has negatively affected physical well being decreased human contact and disadvantaged those unable to drive or unable to afford a car we including state local governments have not invested enough in puvlic transportation to provide access to community services and employment opportunities or even faith communities i think isolation polarization extreme inequities that lead to lack of opportunities for many have contributed to increase in mental health issues i believe we all do better when we all do better i think an unwillingness or resistance to see the systems that underlie many community problems leads some residents to blame those disadvantaged by those systems for their disadvantages acknowledging that systems privilege some and disadvantage others does not mean an individual s own effort and determination are unimportant a willingness to see how the majority population is privileged by a system opens our eyes to see the barriers keeping other neighbors from thriving i do not see us investing enough in our children s well being in the u s to improve community well being overall we have many residents who are food and housing insecure i am encouraged by efforts like point and local efforts focused on early childhood initiatives the dignity respect campaign etc it is great to have community leaders who are intentional about continuous community improvement i think it is important to let encourage all residents be leaders in improving their own lives that is one of the beauties of the design of imagine fox cities being open to all voices with a wide open invitation i do not see enough movement toward a green economy or maintaining of a healthy environment there is much we could do at a local level to plan for sustainability all that said i am a hopeful person i know when people come together for the common good great strides can be made even on seemingly intractable problems i see the many signs in the fox cities of residents coming together to improve the community
